A toy app for evaluating the persuasiveness of arguments.

Compiling requires Opa 1.1.0 or newer (http://opalang.org)

Running requires a server with mongodb (http://mongodb.org)
and nodejs (http://nodejs.org), and a few node npm modules.

Assuming you have the dependencies installed, compiling and
running should be as easy as:
  make
  ./arguments.js

then navigate to port 8080 on your machine (e.g.
http://localhost:8080).

For the time being, there will be a demo install at

 http://arguments.phauna.org/


